-- China’s Pension Fund Balance Increases to $307 Billion
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-06-27T16:15:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/china-s-pension-fund-balance-increases-to-307-billion.html
The balance of  China ’s national
pension fund rose to 1.95 trillion  yuan  ($307 billion) at the
end of 2011, the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Security
said, without giving the year-earlier figure.  Revenue rose 26 percent in 2011 from a year earlier to 1.69
trillion yuan, as expenditure gained 21 percent to 1.28 trillion
yuan, according to a report released by the ministry yesterday.  The national social security system, including the pension
fund and four social-insurance funds, had about 3.02 trillion
yuan in total assets at year-end.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
